Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.51,0:00:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.57,0:00:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello and welcome to what is\Ntonight, a Top Gear Special.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.96,0:00:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's special because it is just one big film.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.16,0:00:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, and to make it, we had to go on holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.61,0:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you say it was a holiday,\Nbut actually it was a fly-drive holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.96,0:00:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't a holiday at all, because,\Nof course, you get to the car hire desk
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the gormless\Nman with the spiky hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.96,0:00:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and he types "War and Peace"\Ninto his computer for 16 hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.96,0:00:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he doesn't know where England is,\Nand he steals your driving licence,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.96,0:00:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he directs you to a car park\Nwhere your car isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.51,0:00:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were going to try and see\Nif we could make it any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.89,0:01:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than suffer the misery of hiring\Na car, maybe it made more sense to buy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.61,0:01:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were each given a budget of $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.11,0:01:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Now, here is\Nthe really clever bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.16,0:01:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of our holiday, which is\Nessentially a road trip across four states,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.65,0:01:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we would see if, instead of simply\Nhaving to hand the hired car back,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.35,0:01:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we could sell our cars and\Nget most of the $1,000 back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.01,0:01:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was brilliant. Now, in the holiday,\Nwe had stones thrown at us by rednecks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.96,0:01:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We crashed into a river full of alligators.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.41,0:01:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What else happened?\NWe had to eat a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.53,0:01:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the big challenge was:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.99,0:01:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we buy a car for less than\Nit cost to rent one for a fortnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.14,0:01:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.33,0:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(1000,124)}Miami, partly sunny\N84 degrees.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.65,0:01:44.65,Music,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,500)}♪ "Sinnerman (Felix Da Housecat's Heavenly House Mix)"\NNina Simone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.65,0:01:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Yes, Miami, home to\Nall the most successful drug dealers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}this year's Mr Big Mac,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.39,0:01:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and Silicon Valley.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.31,0:01:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All very glamorous,\Nbut our journey began here,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:01:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the city's used car lots.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.69,0:02:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is where we had a morning to find\Na set of wheels for less than $1,000.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'd quite like to\Ntake this one for a test drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.97,0:02:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: What's under the bonnet of that?\N- It's a V6.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- V6?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.96,0:02:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Got anything with a V8?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.96,0:02:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- I wanted a muscle car, so I went straight\Nto a dealership that sells Corvettes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.17,0:02:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got the keys?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,400 horsepower, a 5.7-litre V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, how much is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.29,0:02:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,$64,815.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.05,0:02:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,64...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 815.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thousand dollars?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I gave you $1,000 for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:02:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- $1,000?\N- Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.43,0:03:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Richard, it seems,\Nwas being similarly ambitious.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.05,0:03:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much is this? \N- $89,900.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I need something a bit less than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.33,0:03:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- A little bit less than that? \N- Less than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.85,0:03:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- So how much for a Cougar?\N- Cougars are anywhere from 35 to 200,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah...\N- Depending upon the condition and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I need something\Nthat's a bit less than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A bit less than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much for a Challenger?\N- Challengers start at $20,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- $19,900.\N- Less than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Less than that?\N- Less than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,See this here?\NLook, he's turning right on a red light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That is America's only\Ncontribution to Western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.35,0:03:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(964,688)}There's never been a better\Ntime to buy a Johnson...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.96,0:03:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(862,702)}MAY: {\i1}I was the only one using\Neven a modicum of common sense.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.11,0:03:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(878,664)}Would you take $1,000 for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- OK, now, that's going\Nto be a little bit difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.87,0:04:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Soon I took a leaf out\Nof James's book, lowered my sights{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and quickly found a tidy Camaro\N at a place called Adolf's.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,$2,900, this. It's a big ask\Nto get him down to $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.79,0:04:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Might offer him a burger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.23,0:04:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Very popular with murderers, these cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.47,0:04:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}Meanwhile, I'd found\Nsomething we don't have in Britain,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.96,0:04:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a dealership specializing\Nin ex-government cars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.51,0:04:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This will have been a police car,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell by the color,\Nthe hole for the aerial,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.51,0:04:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it says "Police Interceptor" on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this one was\Nprobably, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.30,0:04:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a spy because\Nthere's no badging on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That could have been a Men in Black\Nand that was a Batman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.87,0:04:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, the important thing is\Nthey've all been properly maintained
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm told they're dirt cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And indeed they were, but even\Nthese were beyond my budget.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.19,0:04:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't have anything right now for $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.49,0:04:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Even sensible James was struggling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- I want a real Kojak, smoking...\N- Ah, a real cool car, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- How about a '99 Honda Civic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}CLARKSON: Meanwhile, back at Adolf's,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}negotiations on the Camaro\Nhad broken down.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.43,0:05:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not going well, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought that we'd\Nget here and we'd find
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.81,0:05:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of fantastic old American\N'80s cars for 300 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- I did, I did. I thought we'd just be tripping\Nover Oldsmobile Cutlasses and Firebirds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.71,0:05:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's cause we're buying in that '90s period\Nwhen they were just making rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm looking at a Buick Le Sabre.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.96,0:05:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- God, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.17,0:05:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It was rubbish when it was\Nnew, it was built by idiots
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's rubbish now. I've got...\NYou know, we've got one hour left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit, have we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've reached the\Nbottom end of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.35,0:05:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wouldn't have the Chinese\Nfood around here, let's put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}The fact was, though,\Nif we were going to find cars for $1,000,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.85,0:05:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we'd have to go to an even\Nlower bottom end of the town.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.49,0:06:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How much murdering happens here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- A lot. If you go one mile away\Nhere, if you go to any street...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.63,0:06:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll be murdered.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here, they have guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.19,0:06:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.67,0:06:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's not joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's real, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,.25.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.15,0:06:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Now you see, I wasn't ready for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.41,0:06:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is his other gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.71,0:06:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a shotgun,\NRobert, that's a rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.96,0:06:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's a rifle. This shotgun is\Nsomewhere else, I don't know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And you need this if you're\Ngoing to be a car salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.33,0:06:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy right here, if you go two\Nblocks down here, he got shot five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.11,0:06:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why, by someone buying a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.49,0:06:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- But he killed the guy.\N- He killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He killed the guy, finally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.96,0:06:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- So why have you got\Ntelescopic sights on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they go far\Naway, you just shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the movie John Wayne, the\Nguy is running all the way, like 500 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shoot him right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Hammond.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.75,0:07:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jeremy, how you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.96,0:07:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just been told by my new\Nbest friend, Robert the Persian,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,if you go beyond 79th Street,\Nyou will definitely be murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.17,0:07:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.77,0:07:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond is wearing cowboy boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.73,0:07:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to shoot him, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.39,0:07:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it south or north of 79th Street?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.65,0:07:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.27,0:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided the best plan was\Nto stay on 79th Street itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.37,0:07:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and came across what must be\Nthe most optimistic dealer in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, needs must.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}The lesson\Nwe'd learned already{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was that it was easier\Nto rent a car than buy one,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.59,0:07:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but we weren't giving up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.25,0:07:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me, I'm desperate now.\NI'm desperate for wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:07:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Distressed look on the roof, gunshot holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.96,0:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the car's got a history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.19,0:08:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's massive. Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got a tree growing out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.09,0:08:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been an accident over\Nthere, but the car's still running,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was just wondering if I\Ncould make her an offer for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been ambitious here, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.96,0:08:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This $1,000 is a low amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.65,0:08:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I therefore decided to go\Nbeyond the lower back end of town.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys got any ideas where\NI can find a car for $1,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.96,0:08:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- $1,000? \N- Oh, god, you've got some great teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.69,0:08:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen these teeth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.05,0:08:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You want it today?\N- It's got to be today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. All right, let me get back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.27,0:08:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go right here to the stop sign.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.49,0:08:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hook a right,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,go up exactly two blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.27,0:08:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, what, this way?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.83,0:08:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Amazingly, the tip paid off,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.96,0:08:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I was the first to arrive at\Nour prearranged meeting point.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.71,0:09:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Miami Jai-Alai Stadium.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.63,0:09:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a Chevrolet Camaro, the RS model.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.55,0:09:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Five-liter V8 engine, five-speed\Ngearbox, rear-wheel drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A full-on American muscle car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.39,0:09:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Only three previous murderers,\Nand I only paid $800 for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I am... It's a brilliant,\Nbrilliant, brilliant find.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.67,0:09:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then Hammond turned up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.99,0:09:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear. He's never\Nbeen to America before,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.96,0:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he's bought himself\Nwhat he thinks all Americans have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.96,0:09:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is bluff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.79,0:09:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.96,0:09:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- I knew... Well.\N- It's a Dodge Ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A dent?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.47,0:09:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there's a few dents\Nand bits missing, but it's basic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's basic motoring\Nat its very best.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know how a Mercedes goes?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a Mercedes. It's not a Mercedes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.45,0:10:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much?\N- $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That shuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.07,0:10:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- $1,000?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- $800. I'm already $200 ahead of you.\N- $800?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- The RS model.\N- Was that the basic one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it wasn't the basic one.\NRS is "Rally Sport".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.96,0:10:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd ask James on that one when he\Narrives, but I'm not entirely sure it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.96,0:10:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the RS, the IROC Z...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.23,0:10:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The RS was the...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.45,0:10:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.\N- Yeah, and the Q was the...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.96,0:10:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep quiet about that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.33,0:10:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, every single\Nthing on it works...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.13,0:10:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, it's a manual.\N- Yeah, five on the floor, rear-wheel drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.96,0:10:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a muscle car.\NHow many horsepower?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,200 and a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.96,0:10:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Rubbish.\N- 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,190.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they get such a small\Namount of horsepower from a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.96,0:10:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The more pressing question,\Nthough, was, "Where was James?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.29,0:10:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He will have walked\Ninto a dealership, "Hello",
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.03,0:10:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll have shot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:10:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he take so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.06,0:11:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Because that's what he does.\N- I mean, he'd be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good grief, I thought that was a train!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.15,0:11:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's...\N- Titanic!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.81,0:11:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's a Cadillac!\N- No, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've changed my mind.\NIt's an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.37,0:11:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's really big.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.96,0:11:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That, gentleman, is how you do it.\NIt's a 1989 Cadillac Brougham sedan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.75,0:11:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you think?\N- Well, this is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a long walk round it.\NIt's a really long walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- I like that, though.\N- It doesn't just move up and down, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes straight from side to side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.03,0:11:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have you seen the roads around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.96,0:11:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a perfect car\Nfor the environment. $900!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.43,0:11:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}And you can see why.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's out of repair.\N- Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.96,0:11:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, it's got newspaper in it.\N- You can date it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.96,0:11:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know when it was repaired.\N- It was a Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- What size engine is this thing?\N- Five litre V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not fast, but it is fabulous.\N- You don't say!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not, mate? I took one look and\Nthought, "Oh, it's like a Lotus Exige."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.49,0:12:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}James then turned on our cars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.29,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- The wheels are odd.\N- No, I've got an alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my alloy. Check out my alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.96,0:12:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This has just been made out of bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah!\N- It smells of bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.29,0:12:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, it does smell a bit ripe.\N- Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.27,0:12:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the clothes of\Nthe last person they killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.13,0:12:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last person the driver killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The poor man was trying to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- James and I have bought cars.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.23,0:12:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You've bought a pick-up truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.97,0:12:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the reason yours is in better condition\Nis because it's just a pick-up truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.13,0:12:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's lovely. I'm delighted.\N- I quite like the pick-up truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.93,0:12:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, come on! What, compared to the Camaro?\N- This is the land of the pick-up truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You don't like the Camaro?\N- I'm sorry. I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I do. I mean, one of those\Nin good nick? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.37,0:13:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It isn't.\N- It is... Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.63,0:13:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But every one of us\Nhas got something better
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,than you get from a\Nrental desk at an airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,BOTH: Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}To find out how good\Nour cars were, we were told{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.50,0:13:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to head to a racetrack\N90 miles north of Miami.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.83,0:13:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There we'd be given a series of challenges.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.83,0:13:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in a murderer's muscle\Ncar heading through Miami.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.69,0:13:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.96,0:13:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is brilliant! I love pick-up trucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's... a Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm absolutely staggered!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I've even got a functioning radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Although there's only one station\Nit'll pick up, which is Gospel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.17,0:14:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My God is the\Ntemple of the Holy Spirit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.55,0:14:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.69,0:14:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Jesus Christ is my Lord. My savior...{\i0}\N-Yes, I agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.23,0:14:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(430,656)\i1}Temperatures are a big deal.\NWe're well into the 90s, maybe 100.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mono radio station,\Nhowever, was the tip of an iceberg.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.01,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm honest, there are one\Nor two issues with my Camaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.96,0:14:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The rev counter, for example, broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.96,0:14:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's an alarming knocking\Nnoise from the front suspension
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.39,0:14:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when you go over a bump\Nor when you're on full lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.65,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The others, too, were finding problems.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.41,0:14:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're alone here\Nas I can admit to one or two
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.71,0:14:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,very small faults with my Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.96,0:14:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is that squeak, which is a\Nloose belt or bearing or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.96,0:14:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The other, it is\Nfantastically slow, this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.31,0:14:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing 55 and I'm\Nputting my foot down
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.82,0:14:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm really struggling\Nto get it up to 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.59,0:15:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm honest, it does\Npull a little bit to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.65,0:15:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I brake, it pulls\Nto the left really badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm right behind Richard Hammond's\NDodge Ram and I've just noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for the first time\Nthat the body doesn't line up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[car honks]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wheels quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the worst problem by a\Nmile is the air conditioning, which,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.99,0:15:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can probably see from\Nthe state of my shirt, is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,92% humidity. No air con.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The only consolation I have is that Hammond's\Nair conditioning doesn't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the air conditioning not\Nworking is pretty much perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.43,0:15:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time I've got a\Nradio on one of these trips.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.73,0:15:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}But enough\Nof the car's little foibles.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was time to settle down and enjoy\Nour journey across the Sunshine State.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God, Florida's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.59,0:16:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nasty insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.89,0:16:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Old people, fat people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people who all offer you cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"You want cheese with that?"\N"You want cheese with that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then shoot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.65,0:16:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While Hammond roasted,\NJames remained smug and cool.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.13,0:16:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting a bit parky actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll just turn the\Ntemperature up very slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I'm Burt Reynolds. I'm the bandit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.75,0:16:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Eventually we turned off the highway,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and arrived at the racetrack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.35,0:17:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Moroso Motorsports\NPark is unusual in America{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.13,0:17:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because it has left-handed turns{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and some which go right as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.93,0:17:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps that's why it was deserted,\Ntoo complicated for the colonials.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.27,0:17:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or maybe everyone had been murdered.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.93,0:17:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whatever, it was time\Nfor our first challenge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It says here that each of our cars\Nmust complete one lap of the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The target is one minute, ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Get points for every\Nsecond under that time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lose points\Nfor every second over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But the thing is none of us\Nhave ever seen that track.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's going to be tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're not driving.\N- Well, who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.06,0:17:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say that he's a CIA experiment that\Nwent wrong and that he only eats cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All we know is he's not the Stig,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.45,0:17:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but he is the Stig's American cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.83,0:18:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Stig!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}First, he squeezed himself into my Camaro.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.37,0:18:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,two,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,three,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.47,0:18:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was expecting... \N[imitates tire screeches]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.77,0:18:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,0-60 in 7.9 seconds.\N- Yeah, once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It can do 110 and he's doing that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.13,0:18:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- No more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's limited. It's electronically limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, it's just naturally limited\Nto 110 because it's rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lean that weight in there, Big Stig!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There he goes! One minute,\Nnine seconds on our top stopwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is that good?\N- We don't know, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}What we did know\Nwas that the Pimpmobile was next.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to need a calendar\Nfor this, not a stopwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.96,0:18:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got a diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold this stone\Nand as it's eroded by the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that'll give us an idea\Nof how long he's been.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.65,0:19:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircon Max.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, cock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.93,0:19:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's broken, isn't it, mate?\N- It's run out of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.61,0:19:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}To raise the Titanic,\Nwe borrowed a battery booster.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that for starting your\Nwatch when it stops?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just... Oh, it's begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.19,0:19:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,two,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.01,0:19:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,three,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's moved off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still moving off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.55,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,24 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.99,0:19:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting older.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:19:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks fabulous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.97,0:20:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- C'mon, admit it looks good!\N- We've got plenty of time to admire it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.03,0:20:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Cadillac certainly seemed to\Nsuit Big Stig's relaxed driving style.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.41,0:20:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,, Look at that. On the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.51,0:20:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But would the match made in heaven\Nbe able to beat the Camaro's 1:09?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.03,0:20:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yay!\N- Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.63,0:20:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,1:14.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.87,0:20:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So now it was all down\Nto Hammond's hillbilly mobile.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.79,0:20:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- Three. Go!\N- Let it rip! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.43,0:20:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.73,0:20:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is that manual?\N- Sounds very... Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.69,0:20:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stick shift.\NFour on the floor with overdrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.37,0:20:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Actually,\Nit all looked pretty promising.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.87,0:20:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If this beats mine,\NI'm going to have to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.03,0:20:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am in a Camaro,\Nso don't think that won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.61,0:20:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's a proud and noble thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.79,0:20:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen Brokeback Mountain\Nand thought, "I want a piece of that life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.91,0:20:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"Not that piece. I'll have the pick-up truck."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.61,0:21:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Although the truck had started well,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the last few\Ntight corners it was rubbish.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.96,0:21:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen how my\Nalloy glints in the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- What were you, 1:14?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.45,0:21:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 12, 13...\N- No, it can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 1:14...\N - No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.07,0:21:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.41,0:21:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How could that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,1:16.9!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.96,0:21:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's more to do with\Nthe Stig being too big to get...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't make the turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.23,0:21:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fat Stig's work was done.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And so it was time for the next challenge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.33,0:21:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"You must each accelerate\Nyour car to 50 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"When you reach 50 miles an hour,\Nyou must brake as hard as you can."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a test of acceleration\Nand braking altogether?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.96,0:21:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, "you must brake\Nbefore the end of the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.49,0:21:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"At the end of the track, there is a river...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.15,0:21:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.01,0:21:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"...full of alligators".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.96,0:21:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And that wasn't a misprint.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.31,0:21:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I should explain, that is the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.09,0:22:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look up there, OK, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, and here, this is alligator infested.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.91,0:22:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We drew hot dogs and mine was the shortest.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.47,0:22:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope he doesn't die at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.21,0:22:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's saltwater crocodiles you\Nneed to worry about, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.31,0:22:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I hope he doesn't go\Nin the river, that would be awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.67,0:22:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell with the clutch!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.37,0:22:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit had started.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.96,0:22:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, 30, I don't want\Nto be eaten by an alligator.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.79,0:22:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,35, 40, 45, it's 50!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.29,0:22:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's doubly disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.51,0:22:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one, he's not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.29,0:22:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And number two,\Nthe fastest accelerating car here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.59,0:22:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,only just stopped before the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.31,0:22:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Surely though, the huggy bear mobile would\Nstruggle to do 0-50-0 in the distance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.11,0:22:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.31,0:23:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That is movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.31,0:23:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, car!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.71,0:23:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on,\Ncome on, I'm nearly there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.45,0:23:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Brake!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.96,0:23:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Strewth! That had me worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.96,0:23:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I should imagine he's clenched in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.91,0:23:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight tons of Caddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.41,0:23:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was really nervous.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.05,0:23:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd just seen Big Stig try to\Nstop my truck and fail completely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.07,0:23:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, it's 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.67,0:23:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here he comes to a certain death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.96,0:23:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,40, 45, it takes ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.96,0:23:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is quite funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.97,0:23:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.11,0:23:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.96,0:23:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alligators, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.96,0:23:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I suggest we may\Nhave made them angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.33,0:23:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just driven in their-\Ninto their living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.96,0:24:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Such an unsufferable oaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.41,0:24:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's my pick-up, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.43,0:24:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The cars had survived\Ntheir ordeal by track just...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the next morning, the real test began.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.25,0:24:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A sweltering 800-mile\Nroad trip to New Orleans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.45,0:24:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Today, partly cloudy, highs in the\Nlower 90s, chance of thunderstorms 30%.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.97,0:24:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Things started badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.96,0:24:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Engine starts]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.47,0:24:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: Has it got petrol in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.69,0:24:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: Yeah, look, it's full.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.61,0:24:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, yeah, but has it got petrol in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.53,0:24:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.96,0:24:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When did you last put petrol in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.13,0:24:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Miami.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.13,0:25:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you come to mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.96,0:25:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stupid man!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.96,0:25:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a five-litre V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.96,0:25:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.41,0:25:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- The car is fine. What's happened is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mine's run out of electricity again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.17,0:25:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.41,0:25:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can I borrow your van and the jump leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.91,0:25:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- See how prepared we are on this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.21,0:25:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You had the leads in your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.11,0:25:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, no, you had the leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.39,0:25:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not a stupid man.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.03,0:25:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: I've got a door panel,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.75,0:25:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some bolts, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.11,0:25:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.63,0:25:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: He's lost the jump leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.96,0:25:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's lost the jump leads.\N- He's lost the jump leads! He has lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.19,0:25:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't going well, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.43,0:25:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're thinking of coming\Nto America, this is what it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.96,0:25:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got your Comfort Inn,\Nyou've got your Best Western
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.39,0:25:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got your Red Lobster where you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.61,0:25:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's very fat, everybody's\Nvery stupid, and everybody's very rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.79,0:25:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the Holiday\Nprogramme, it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.47,0:25:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Eventually, the leads were found,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.27,0:26:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and Hammond positioned\Nhimself for the jump start.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.23,0:26:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: No, it's not funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.96,0:26:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.23,0:26:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: We're off!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.29,0:26:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sweating already.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.96,0:26:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, I'm not going to be for much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.96,0:26:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not a sunny day, it's\Njust a humid day today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.37,0:26:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.96,0:26:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tropical.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.31,0:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's the approach of a cold front.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.45,0:26:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's tall human limbs for the height.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.96,0:26:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[THEY LAUGH]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.79,0:26:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bigger than you expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.47,0:26:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't feel like...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.25,0:26:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to know what\NHammond thinks he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.96,0:26:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Chewing gum, his aviators, his\Ncowboy hat and his pick-up truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.21,0:26:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: {\i1}To help relieve\Nthe tedium of the journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.69,0:26:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the production office had\Nprovided us with CB radios,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.96,0:27:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and for those we needed\Nappropriate call signs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.53,0:27:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Brokeback, Brokeback. This is Murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.13,0:27:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Brokeback,\Nto Murderer and The Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.96,0:27:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[Incomprehensible chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.13,0:27:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why these CB radios\Nnever caught on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.96,0:27:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Braker, breaker,\None-nine, contact, eyeball
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.39,0:27:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,10-10 till we do it again, Captain Slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.45,0:27:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[Incomprehensible chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.87,0:27:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's there and I can't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.96,0:27:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was hopeless, so we changed channels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.59,0:27:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, I'm 22. Are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.89,0:27:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yo, big boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.35,0:27:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And finally made contact with a native.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.96,0:27:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Radio chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.96,0:27:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's him in that truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.17,0:27:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's asking...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.37,0:27:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's asking another lorry driver where he\Nmight find a lady friend for the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Radio chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.96,0:28:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All they've got to talk about on that CB\Nis the weather and prostitutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.96,0:28:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's raining, I'm going north\Nand I'm looking for a hooer".
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.45,0:28:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}As we headed northwest,\Nthe heat and humidity became unbearable.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.01,0:28:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sitting there in the winter,\Nyou can't imagine what it's like
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.71,0:28:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to be in an un-air-conditioned\Ncar in Florida now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.85,0:28:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.35,0:28:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Danger persists in the hot west.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.96,0:28:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though almost a quarter\Nof the fire is contained,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.73,0:28:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}much of it is still burning out of control.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.29,0:28:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Only the\Ninsufferable May wasn't suffering.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.65,0:28:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chaps, it's May here, just to\Nlet you know that my air conditioning{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.13,0:28:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is working very nicely\Nat 65 degrees Fahrenheit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.29,0:28:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.33,0:28:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}But then,\Nthe smile was wiped from his face...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.75,0:28:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.23,0:29:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought you some presents.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.96,0:29:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got you a steak and cheese biscuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.33,0:29:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- And I've brought you a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.17,0:29:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Really?\N- Yeah. We've got fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.96,0:29:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's fantastic, mate!\N- How do you feel now?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.96,0:29:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, air-con, there it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.39,0:29:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,[THEY LAUGH]
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.01,0:29:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I've got?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.09,0:29:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ham and cheese, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.35,0:29:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dundee, ham and cheese",\NI'll read you the ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.61,0:29:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Blah, blah, blah, blah...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.93,0:29:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and "Imitation American cheese".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.81,0:29:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- So it's the only thing that hasn't\Nactually got any cheese on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.35,0:29:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.67,0:29:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After our Imitation American lunch, it\Nwas my turn to help the stricken Cadillac.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.53,0:29:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.19,0:29:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm back in the sweatbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.63,0:29:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(974,656)}Excessive heat\Nwarnings continuing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.41,0:30:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what that is doing is just\Nturbocharging warm air into my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.27,0:30:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.96,0:30:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, this is Brokeback.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.47,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you cut the wire?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.67,0:30:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(426,680)\i1}You want your man to look good,\Nbut words like exfoliant scare him?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.01,0:30:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}The miles passed,\Nwith the Cadillac endlessly breaking down.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.47,0:30:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.96,0:30:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have you got the leads?\N- No, you've got the leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.47,0:30:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(318,682)\i1}Offers to qualified buyers\Non select models.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.75,0:30:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Still, thanks to\Nthe automatic windscreen washes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.51,0:30:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at Florida service stations...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.69,0:30:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.96,0:30:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...Hammond and I could at least enjoy some refreshing showers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.25,0:30:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}while he got it going again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.67,0:31:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Cadillac, however, was\Nnot the only trouble-maker.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.35,0:31:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After just 200 miles, my Camaro\Nwas hardly tip-top either.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.33,0:31:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, sit-rep on the Camaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.96,0:31:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the headlights are working,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.26,0:31:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the dashboard has come off,\Nall the dials are broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.39,0:31:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one radio speaker remains,\Nhowever, and it's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.39,0:31:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(836,682)}The good news is that with God's help,\Nwe can stop global warming.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.43,0:31:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(262,656)\i1}In a world where\Ntails stop wagging,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.95,0:31:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(330,654)\i1}sticks don't get fetched,\Nand chew toys stay dry,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.47,0:31:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(374,664)\i1}one man dares to step\Nforward and declare...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.59,0:31:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(984,664)}I can get to the root of\Nyour dog's depression.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.73,0:31:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Eventually, our Top Gear fly-drive\Nholiday convoy reached the 300-mile mark.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.19,0:31:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And as a reward, the production\Noffice gave each of us $100{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.96,0:31:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to buy an accessory that might in\Nsome way make our journey less arduous.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.19,0:32:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hoping and praying that James\Nhad bought a new battery for{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.39,0:32:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}his stupid Cadillac, we all\Nmet up to show off our new toys.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.21,0:32:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- A trailer?\N- No, a Freedom Grill 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.55,0:32:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- A grilling system?\N- It's a grilling system.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.21,0:32:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[CLARKSON LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.43,0:32:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.83,0:32:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- No! \N- No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.21,0:32:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.49,0:32:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop tailgate, cooking platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.13,0:32:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.83,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordon Ramsay hasn't got\Nanything like that in his kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.96,0:32:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got anything that good, James?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.19,0:32:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.96,0:32:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I got...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.67,0:32:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a clothes rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.69,0:32:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- Look at my perfectly pressed linen jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.29,0:32:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- He has a linen jacket on a clothes rack.\N- Don't wobble it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.96,0:32:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, so you step into your car,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.69,0:32:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and here, if you look, is a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.81,0:32:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- In your car?\N- Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.61,0:32:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- But where do you get the water from, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.50,0:32:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- It comes from the cool box\Nin the back, this tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.96,0:32:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you just plug this\Ninto the cigarette lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.99,0:33:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,hit that button, refreshing shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.01,0:33:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you're jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.69,0:33:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(814,704)}Sadly, though, our dreams\Nof luxury living were shattered{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.09,0:33:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(814,704)}when we received\Nthe next challenge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.96,0:33:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(814,704)}"Tonight, you will be camping."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.96,0:33:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.41,0:33:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"And you are only allowed to eat what\Nyou find dead at the side of the road."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.19,0:33:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What, you mean roadkill?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.77,0:33:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're only allowed...\NIt's on the... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.09,0:33:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's animals that we find\Nby the side of the road dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.23,0:33:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's our supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.57,0:33:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, just think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.95,0:33:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can prepare the food,\Nlike for cooking, wash it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.96,0:33:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can then cook it.\NJames can dress for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.01,0:33:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(800,682)\i1}- Potatoes, tomatoes, it's a lot to know.\N- I can see that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.49,0:33:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(878,674)\i1}So let me ask you, how high should\Na pineapple bounce when it's ripe?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.99,0:33:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, sit-rep.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.41,0:33:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The power steering pump\Nreally is on its last legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.99,0:33:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a terrible wheel wobble.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.43,0:34:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm cool for the\Nfirst time since I set off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.19,0:34:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am cool now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.67,0:34:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To increase our chances\Nof finding some roadkill,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.18,0:34:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we swapped the\Ninterstate for smaller roads.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.71,0:34:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And very quickly, we got lucky.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.96,0:34:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What on the right? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.69,0:34:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.79,0:34:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't fancy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.27,0:34:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}No matter, though,\Nbecause further down the road{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.97,0:34:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I came across a\Nfresh and tasty possum.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.03,0:34:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.19,0:34:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,James, don't run over it, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.81,0:34:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You blithering idiot, you just run over it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.01,0:34:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not edible now, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.07,0:34:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For flattening our supper,\NJames was punished.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.39,0:35:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Eventually, we did find fresh\Nmeat, but it was a bit too fresh.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.73,0:35:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: I thought\Nyou were going to run it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.61,0:35:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, even I wouldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.25,0:35:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do that, tortoise!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.41,0:35:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you have wild...\NThere's no wild tortoises.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.89,0:35:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, they've got to be somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.46,0:35:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's escaped from\Nsome eight-year-old girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.73,0:35:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- How does a tortoise escape?\NCome back, come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.97,0:35:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(852,702)}Finally, though,\Nten miles down the road...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.45,0:35:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(902,702)}We've got dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.19,0:35:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Squirrel.\N- Check that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.63,0:35:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that with a bit of\Ncheese will be delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.29,0:35:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at May's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.96,0:35:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I never told you about\Nmy vegetarianism, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.79,0:35:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Soon,\Nwe were near the field{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.83,0:35:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}where we would be\Ncamping for the night.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.33,0:35:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the sun's going down,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.75,0:36:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm with my mates,\Nit's down below 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.96,0:36:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in the Deep South.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.45,0:36:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pleasant evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.35,0:36:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.99,0:36:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we still only had a squirrel for\Ndinner, so I peeled off for one last forage{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.16,0:36:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}while the others went ahead to set up camp.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.09,0:36:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.23,0:36:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, we've got work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.23,0:36:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking squirrel on the rack,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.91,0:36:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and then maybe, here's my plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.11,0:36:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with a few herbs garnished,\Nsomething like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.87,0:36:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking if I cook it once,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.95,0:36:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and then maybe cook it again,\Nso it'll go like crispy duck,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.69,0:36:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,only it's a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.39,0:36:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he ever coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.51,0:36:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just lob it on, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.59,0:36:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, well, with a rabbit, you take the\Nhead off, you go down the middle...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.96,0:37:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But all we've got to\Ndo it with is a tent peg.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.96,0:37:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you bring a penknife?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.23,0:37:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Time passed, and still no sign of Jeremy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.27,0:37:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not peeling it, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.65,0:37:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see why I should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.05,0:37:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on.\N- I don't want to peel a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.01,0:37:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to bring it over to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.71,0:37:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is that a car?\N- Is it Jezza?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.11,0:37:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,James?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.96,0:37:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's he got?\N- In all seriousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.13,0:37:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.69,0:37:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.75,0:37:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You have got to be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.67,0:37:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a flaming cow, mate!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.15,0:37:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Main course.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.23,0:38:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.09,0:38:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking how long I've been\Nin the sun putting that tent up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.41,0:38:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why?\N- Because what I'm seeing...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.33,0:38:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[HAMMOND LAUGHS] You'll love this...\Nis a cow on the roof of your Camaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.05,0:38:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- It is, isn't it? There is a cow on there.\N- It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.41,0:38:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I don't want to be\Npedantic, but is it roadkill?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.85,0:38:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What, are you suggesting I ran it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.96,0:38:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well... \N- Check out the front of my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.96,0:38:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to find someone to help me\Nget it on there, but I didn't run it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.28,0:38:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at the side of the road,\Nnow it's on the roof and it's our supper!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.71,0:38:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.17,0:38:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll, we've got to...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.29,0:38:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Peel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.47,0:38:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not peeling that!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.25,0:38:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: {\i1}First, though,\Nwe had to get it off the roof.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.41,0:38:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I go round a corner\Nquite quickly, backwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.71,0:38:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Um, left hand down, yeah.\N- If I reverse... left hand down,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.05,0:38:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll roll over that way, do we think?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.83,0:38:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I reckon she's good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.35,0:38:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.19,0:38:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, Jeremy!\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.96,0:38:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm better, I can't see a cow\Non the roof of your Camaro anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.87,0:38:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not hungry.\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.67,0:38:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.65,0:38:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.29,0:39:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It stinks, Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.81,0:39:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, Brokeback and I feasted\Non beef and squirrel
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.96,0:39:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, with May in bed, we decided\Nit would be better for all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.96,0:39:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if the air conditioning\Nin his car were to break.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.29,0:39:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Shhh!\N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.91,0:39:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[WHISPERS] Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.23,0:39:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we just hit it with a hammer?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.23,0:39:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[HAMMOND LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.01,0:39:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.96,0:39:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.75,0:39:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[THEY LAUGH]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.47,0:39:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They really built\Nthese old buses, it's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.67,0:39:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[CLARKSON LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.31,0:39:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just hitting it with a spatula.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.32,0:39:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Another mosquito just bit my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.55,0:39:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.15,0:39:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[CLARKSON LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.27,0:40:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to notice, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.55,0:40:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[BOTH LAUGH]
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.41,0:40:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Another humid day dawned,\Nand now May knew what it felt like.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.21,0:40:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Those pathetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.75,0:40:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,lager-swilling, barbecuing, redneck\Nthugs that I call my co-presenters
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.61,0:40:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,have vandalized my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.65,0:40:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have had to make a few\Nmodifications to the car this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.59,0:40:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the cow incident,\NI lost the aerial,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.83,0:40:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so now I've got an iStation instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.96,0:40:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, teamed with the fan,\Nmeans I really can't see where I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.96,0:40:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, because some cow did get into\Nthe car, I'm using air fresheners here
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.33,0:40:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to cover up the smell,\Nso I can't really see where I've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.05,0:40:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and, um, the passenger seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.37,0:41:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That got a lot of cow juice on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.31,0:41:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's now in the back of Hammond's truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.51,0:41:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(862,690)}By this afternoon,\Nskies will be considerably cloudy{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.31,0:41:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(916,690)}with showers\Nand thunderstorms likely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.41,0:41:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(862,688)}Northeast winds, 5-10 mph.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.93,0:41:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.96,0:41:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alabama's only 40 miles now!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.63,0:41:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our scrapyard cars had covered 650 miles,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.96,0:41:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and, inevitably, they were\Nbecoming more than just metal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.31,0:41:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole thing now really\Nsums up why I love cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.46,0:41:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, take this Camaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.53,0:41:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The dash is more plastic\Nthan an American newsreader.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.25,0:41:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The engine's got less power than Belgium,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.51,0:41:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the suspension is softer than the\Njournalism in an in-flight magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.87,0:41:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course, it reeks of cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.45,0:41:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I adore it, because...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.35,0:41:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you can just sense it wants to keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.53,0:41:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I bet James is exactly the same\Nthere in the Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.73,0:42:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet he's having exactly the same emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.96,0:42:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be in this now\Nthan an Enzo, and I'm not joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.29,0:42:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}But before we entered Alabama,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.47,0:42:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we had to go to Bagdad\Nfor our next challenge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.89,0:42:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.49,0:42:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in Bagdad.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.53,0:42:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a place I was expecting\Nto visit on this trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.27,0:42:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Challenge time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.21,0:42:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Lose five pounds in one hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.13,0:42:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, sweat it away! Come on then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.07,0:42:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.96,0:42:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, it says here\Nwe must not be shot or arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.72,0:42:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as we drive across\Nthe proud state of Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.63,0:43:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But we will get bonus points if we can\Nget one of the others shot or arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.93,0:43:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand, how do we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.81,0:43:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You will therefore decorate\None another's cars in such a way
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.83,0:43:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to draw maximum attention to yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.97,0:43:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in this Bible-bashing, redneck,\Ndeeply Christian part of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.11,0:43:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Decorate?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.63,0:43:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I think what it means is we each have\Nto write slogans on the other cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.47,0:43:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- So you...\N- To get them killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.16,0:43:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.\N- All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.55,0:43:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you do Hammond's,\Ntake it away into the bushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.93,0:43:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- You do... \N- I'm doing yours. I'm getting you killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.33,0:43:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, come on!\N- I've got another idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.75,0:43:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The South, The South...\NIt's, it's Christian, short hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't like communists...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.69,0:43:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What is closest to their heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.36,0:43:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to get him killed, this is\Na once in a lifetime opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.15,0:43:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be letting you down,\Nme down, everybody down.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.09,0:43:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[MAY LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.43,0:43:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Revenge for all those height gags.\NEvery time he's called me Hamster.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.57,0:43:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for every time\Nyou've been late and lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.63,0:44:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell what it says yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.39,0:44:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,James, I hate you for that.\NI really hate you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.47,0:44:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just think about all the times\Nyou drove into the back of my Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.81,0:44:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.\N- Do you know, actually, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.83,0:44:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, we've all done a good job here,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.05,0:44:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do believe that the\Nperson most likely to be shot
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.64,0:44:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is indeed Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.21,0:44:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think what you've done there,\NJames, is killed your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.05,0:44:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.63,0:44:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Gingerly,\Nwe rejoined the open road.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.29,0:44:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Three religions down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.55,0:44:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,George Bush,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.21,0:44:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,God, country and western.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.43,0:44:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.63,0:44:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ascending order.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.97,0:45:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.25,0:45:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have felt less conspicuous than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.59,0:45:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are, sweet home Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.19,0:45:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[IMITATES GUNFIRE]
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.65,0:45:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They've shot their own sign!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.53,0:45:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they going to do to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.43,0:45:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand what Jeremy\Nhas actually done to my car
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.53,0:45:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to remember\Nthat this is deep Republican territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.23,0:46:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman is the arch-Democrat.\NShe is the Antichrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.96,0:46:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just the slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.63,0:46:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fact that it's painted on a pick-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.21,0:46:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a symbol of the South. I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.67,0:46:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[HORN BLARES]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.96,0:46:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.55,0:46:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, Jeremy has written\Non the boot, "NASCAR sucks".
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.11,0:46:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's a type of saloon car racing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.83,0:46:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that is very, very big\Nin this part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.01,0:46:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where all the drivers come from,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.96,0:46:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all the building of the cars is done,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.61,0:46:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all the supporters come from\Ndown here, and to say it sucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.11,0:46:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is a bit like going up and punching\Nsomebody's sainted mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.85,0:46:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.27,0:46:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.96,0:46:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Car honks]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.77,0:46:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}We'd survived the highway,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.97,0:46:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but then we had to pull into a town for fuel.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.81,0:47:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is really terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.17,0:47:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.83,0:47:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.85,0:47:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's diesel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.31,0:47:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... I've gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.96,0:47:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hillary for President" - that's...\Nthat's not going down well.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.11,0:47:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This lady was cross, but not\Nas cross as the garage's owner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.71,0:47:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,... I'll ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.97,0:47:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, are y'all gay, looking to see how long\Nit takes to get beat up in a hick town?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.13,0:47:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: I'm not gay, I'm married.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.77,0:47:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got three children.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.39,0:47:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: Er, no, we're not. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.37,0:47:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We just sort of decorated\Nour cars in a distinctive manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.97,0:47:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"NASCAR sucks",\N"Country and Western is rubbish"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.49,0:47:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess what, you're in a hick town, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.96,0:47:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna die now, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.63,0:47:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare! [Beep]
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.71,0:47:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She said she was gonna get "the boys".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.17,0:47:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.41,0:48:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we decided to scarper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.73,0:48:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just remembered,\NI've actually got loads of petrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.21,0:48:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}And then, of all the moments...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.79,0:48:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oi, jump leads!\N- You're joking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.27,0:48:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jump leads.\N- Not now!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.11,0:48:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is gonna be\Nthe quickest jump in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.57,0:48:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they?\NYou get the leads, I'll start it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.13,0:48:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell your friend if he\Ntears up my parking lot again...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.47,0:48:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The rednecks arrived.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.83,0:48:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We've just got a slight problem here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.45,0:48:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[Beep]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.81,0:48:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.83,0:48:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then, they turned on the film crews.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.19,0:48:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[Beep] Hey! If he tears...\Nif you tear up my parking lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.85,0:48:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick! [Engine starts]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.43,0:48:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Rocks started pelting our vans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.15,0:48:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Five...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.29,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,four, get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.77,0:48:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.27,0:49:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[Beep]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.01,0:49:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For the next few moments, our TV\Nprogram became a radio show.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(338,678)}CLARKSON: {\i1}Oh, [Bleep],\Nthere are the pick-up trucks.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.69,0:49:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(482,680)}Can you get your foot down?\NI think we've got a load of them on our tail.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.69,0:49:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,680)}{\i1}Something's going on here,\NI'm telling you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.11,0:49:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,678)}{\i1}Because these three trucks\Nthat were in the petrol station{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.13,0:49:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(345,678)}{\i1}have now just torn past us.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.15,0:49:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(944,660)}HAMMOND: {\i1}We need to\Nget these slogans off, lads.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.93,0:49:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pull over, pull over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.85,0:49:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.96,0:49:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have nothing to wipe it off with now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.96,0:49:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}With the artwork\Ngone, we hit the road... hard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.93,0:50:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing something I never thought I'd do,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.29,0:50:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am running for the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.96,0:50:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,God in heaven,\Nthat was actually frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.41,0:50:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They could have killed us!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.79,0:50:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They really do have an irony deficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.47,0:50:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly believe that\Nin certain parts of America now,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.36,0:50:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,people have started\Nto mate with vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.75,0:50:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then, with one problem behind us,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.13,0:50:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we ran straight into another.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.73,0:50:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.11,0:50:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think this is God punishing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.91,0:50:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.11,0:50:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[Thunders]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.19,0:50:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.96,0:50:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a great time to discover that the\Nwipers in my car were worse than useless.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.51,0:50:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like something\Nout of a horror film now.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.79,0:50:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in serious trouble,\NI cannot see a damn thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.91,0:51:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There were no exits and{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.15,0:51:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}stopping on the hard shoulder\Nin rain like this would have been suicidal,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.96,0:51:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so there was only one choice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.37,0:51:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You're out of lane. Go right, Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.33,0:51:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, now, this is... very bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.25,0:51:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Left a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.15,0:51:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop raining, please stop\Nraining, please stop raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.43,0:51:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're out of lane, go right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.37,0:51:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- I think I'm just going\Nto get out and kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.29,0:51:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Put myself out of my misery...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.97,0:51:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hell's teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.61,0:51:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What with the storm\Nand the rock-throwing rednecks,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.61,0:51:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}our fly-drive holiday\Nwasn't going that well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.63,0:51:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to get on the big British jet and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.75,0:51:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be met by a homosexual\Nin grey flannel trousers saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"Welcome on board,\NMr. Clarkson. Can I get you a scone?"
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.96,0:52:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,111 miles to New Orleans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.83,0:52:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Camaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.96,0:52:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it!\NWe're in Louisiana!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.01,0:52:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: {\i1}All we had to do was\Nget there and sell our cars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.41,0:52:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And that, actually,\Nwould be quite a sad moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.81,0:52:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I love my Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.73,0:52:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we've know\Neach other, what, a few days
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.93,0:52:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've had this\Nfantastic adventure together
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.77,0:52:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all across America and it's my car now,\NI know all it's foibles.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.61,0:52:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the biggest truck, it's not\Nthe fastest, it's not the best looking
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.43,0:52:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but it just keeps going.\NIt's like a little Welsh pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.67,0:53:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.47,0:53:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This car really is like\Nliving in an old house.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.73,0:53:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know to kick the back door\Nin a certain way to make it open.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.09,0:53:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same with this. I know how\Nto keep the power steering going.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.53,0:53:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how to get the best\Nout of what's left of the clutch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.96,0:53:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it as a kind of joke\Nwhen we started, but now...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.95,0:53:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we're like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.96,0:53:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Crossing the central\NReservation [Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.41,0:53:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: {\i1}Of course there were certain\Nother problems with selling our cars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.96,0:53:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got some very, very bad Cadillac weave
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.17,0:53:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,going on on this straight stretch here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.45,0:53:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll keep the worry beads to hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.21,0:53:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.67,0:53:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in New Orleans and something\Nhas come off the Camaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.06,0:54:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperature gauge is off the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.23,0:54:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.09,0:54:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,MAY: {\i1}Finally, though, we made it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.96,0:54:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And my word,\Nwere we in for a shock.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.13,0:54:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We had seen on the news\Nwhat Hurricane Katrina had done{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.96,0:54:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but seeing the devastation\Nfor real was truly astonishing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.95,0:54:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.59,0:54:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.57,0:54:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now this is extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.51,0:54:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every house... I've been\Ndriving now, what, 15 miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.96,0:54:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a pavement,\Nthere isn't a building,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.33,0:54:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't anything\Nthat isn't smashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.49,0:54:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such a vast scale of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.75,0:54:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A year had passed\Nsince Katrina had blown through{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.11,0:54:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we sort of assumed\Nthat after 12 months,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.59,0:54:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the wealthiest nation\Non Earth would have fixed it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.83,0:54:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but we were wrong.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.63,0:55:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How can the rest of America\Nsleep at night
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.35,0:55:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}knowing that this is here?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.53,0:55:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It certainly gave us a problem.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.55,0:55:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The original plan had been\Nfor us to sell our cars here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.55,0:55:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and see who could get the most money.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.87,0:55:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But in the midst of all this\Nthat just seemed... wrong.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.51,0:55:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We, therefore, had a conflab{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.45,0:55:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and decided that we\Nshould give our cars away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.19,0:55:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we called a local mission\Nwho put us in touch with some families{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.86,0:55:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who'd lost theirs in Katrina.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.75,0:55:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got an alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.01,0:55:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all standard, it's not\Nbeing messed with in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.35,0:55:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the guy who had this before,\Nit's in 150,000 miles and look,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.67,0:55:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like new under there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.11,0:55:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- I like it.\N- Done, it's yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.87,0:55:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the truck, it's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.96,0:55:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Look after it, it's been\Na good friend to me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.29,0:55:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.55,0:55:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,HAMMOND: {\i1}Jeremy did\Nhis usual trick of telling it like it is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.03,0:56:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Rev counter - not good,\Nspeedo - not good,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.35,0:56:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,fuel gauge - not good,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.96,0:56:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dent on the roof -\Nthat was caused by a cow,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.79,0:56:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as driving it is concerned,\Nthe engine is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.09,0:56:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Gearbox - tip top!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.29,0:56:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good car, it's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.73,0:56:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So, although it hadn't\Nbeen the most relaxing holiday,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.87,0:56:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it had been a proper Boys' Own adventure.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.85,0:56:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And what's more, we could go home\Nknowing that we'd done a little bit{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.57,0:56:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to help those\Nless fortunate than ourselves.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.96,0:56:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, Richard and I could,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.69,0:56:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but James sadly couldn't\Neven give his car away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.95,0:56:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still here!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.37,0:57:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A family came around this corner,\Nnot ten minutes ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.15,0:57:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh thank you, we lost\Neverything in Hurricane Katrina..."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.97,0:57:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And they rejected it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.27,0:57:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want a lift\Nto the airport in my car?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.85,0:57:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- No, me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.55,0:57:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't.\N- I walk, thank you, ta-ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.59,0:57:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond, can I borrow the jump leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.43,0:57:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.13,0:57:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.81,0:57:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.97,0:57:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Loser, loser!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.23,0:57:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.59,0:57:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I reckon, if you look on Google Earth,\Nyou'll see his car, cos it'll still be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.97,0:57:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not like you won't be able\Nto see it either. It's big enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.77,0:57:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so there's no doubt that\NJames lost that challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.96,0:57:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and equally no doubt that I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.65,0:57:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,\NHang on, how'd you arrive at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.83,0:57:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my Camaro was the fastest,\Nit had the best brakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.83,0:57:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it didn't break down,\Napart from the wipers... much,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.77,0:57:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.38,0:58:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't actually quite as easy to give away\Nas you made out in that film, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.77,0:58:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you tell the ladies\Nand gentlemen what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.49,0:58:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- after the cameras had been turned off?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.73,0:58:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a lady came and\Nshe said she was a lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.28,0:58:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,representing the Christian\Nmission that we'd gone to,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.96,0:58:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said she'd been promised\Nby one of our researchers a '91 Camaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.57,0:58:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was a '89, and she said\Nthat was misrepresentation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.49,0:58:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was going to sue me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.95,0:58:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this... It really\Ndid happen, it really did.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.59,0:58:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, she said\Nthat if I gave her $20,000 in cash
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.69,0:58:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,she might be able\Nto make the case go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.27,0:58:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you won't believe\Nwhat happened to us next.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.79,0:58:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, which was that a very,\Nvery large pick-up turned up,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.17,0:58:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,full of heavily armed and very burly men,\Ntold us to get off their street.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.47,0:58:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah!\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.57,0:58:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So really we do have two Top Gear\Ntop tips for you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.96,0:58:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One - yes, you can buy rather than rent,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.60,0:58:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and two - don't go to America!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.25,0:58:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Top Gear's back to its normal self\Nnext week, so we'll see you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.57,0:58:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for watching. Good night!
